unit;` work identically. The `\"runner\": \"VSTest\"` setting in `global.json` is specific to `dotnet test`, so I'll need to adjust that for the new runner configuration. I need to clarify what `global.json` actually contains—the `\"test\"` section with `\"runner\"` is a newer feature, and for xUnit v3 it wouldn't use VSTest anyway. Let me move forward with the migration plan: updating the `.csproj` file, keeping the test code largely unchanged since basic Fact and Assert patterns work the same, adjusting `global.json`, then building and testing to verify everything works.","outputTokens":1179,"requestId":"0BC5:303A77:6C3551:7E5F47:69F010F3"},"id":"61b5d532-fd83-4df8-a224-66b74c4ccc00","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:44:43.706Z","parentId":"4827e967-1490-42f0-801e-8701d8d6cae1"}
